Jones </PERSON> is in control,'' <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramsey </PERSON> said. He said <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> might not be able to deliver the votes or might not want to support a mainstream Democrat. <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> also will have little power to set priorities for the local party. `` He will carry the title and preside over the meetings, but he wo n't set the agenda. He ca n't stray from the agenda, either,'' <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramsey </PERSON> said. For now, <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> said he is n't sure of his plans except that he wants to bring more people into the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> during his term. His attorney says they have n't ruled out a possible return to court. Despite the squabbles, <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> has done one good thing, says <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Stanley </PERSON>, a past county chairwoman: `` He has united the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Harris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION>.''
