Saturday's win brought New Trier its eighth consecutive crown in the contest and also pitted two schools whose rivalry is fierce _ in the classroom and the playing field. <PERSON> Rhoad </PERSON> called this year's event the `` battle of the giants'' because <LOCATION> Evanston </LOCATION> and New Trier placed high in a national written math contest in March. Of the 14,000 schools entered, <LOCATION> Evanston </LOCATION> placed first, a Canadian school placed second and <PERSON> New </PERSON> <PERSON> Trier </PERSON> was third. At the weekend contest here, students competed in 13 events, including a relay in which each member of a four-student team worked on one-fourth of the problem.
