<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Astrophysicist <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> <PERSON> Lizhi </PERSON>, an outspoken critic of Marxism in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, published or edited five scientific works last year, an authoritative weekly said today in a lengthy article chronicling <PERSON> Fang </PERSON>'s academic achievements. `` Writing and editing five books in one year is my record,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Beijing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Review </ORGANIZATION> quoted <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> as saying. `` It may be the result of my concentrated effort.'' One of the books, `` Creation of Cosmology,'' was co-published with his wife <PERSON> Li </PERSON> <PERSON> Shuxian </PERSON>, a physics teacher at <ORGANIZATION> Beijing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>, where the couple live. <PERSON> Fang </PERSON>, 52, was expelled from the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and fired from his job as vice president of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Science </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technology </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Anhui </LOCATION> province in January 1987 after being accused of inciting students to stage pro-democracy demonstrations. The official media, however, has stressed in several pieces on <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> that he enjoys academic freedom at the <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Observatory </LOCATION>, where he has been working since last year. Since losing his university job `` for outspokenly advocating bourgeois liberalist views,'' the <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> Review said, `` <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> has achieved a great deal in his research work.'' The article said <PERSON> Fang </PERSON> was allowed to visit <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> for the 12th time last summer for academic activities, during which he reached an agreement with the <LOCATION> Italian </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </OR