<HEAD>Salvador's Legislature Paralyzed By Vote Dispute</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DOUGLAS GRANT MINE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The governing party's presidential candidate on Monday appealed to the rightist opposition to help resolve a crisis that has split the legislature `` There is either going to be consensus or permanent impasse for three years. And the country can not withstand impasse,'' <PERSON> Adolfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Rey </PERSON> <PERSON> Prendes </PERSON>, nominated at the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION>' convention on Friday, told a news conference. The crisis stems from a dispute over which party controls one seat in the 60-seat <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION>, the unicameral legislature that was elected March 20. The right-wing <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, or <PERSON> Arena </PERSON>, claims it won 31 seats during the election and that the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION>, who had previously held a majority, stole a seat through electoral fraud. The Christian Democrats deny the charge. <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> has appealed the final vote count for the disputed seat to the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, but it was uncertain when the court would rule. The rightists maintain that, for the moment, the Assembly has 59 members. The legislature was to have been inaugurated Sunday for a three-year term. The 30 Arena deputies showed up and declared congress in session. But the 30 other deputies _ 23 for the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION> and seven for the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conciliation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> _ gathered in another room and held their own session. The Christian Democrats claimed the legislature no longer exists because the constitution says that `` half plus one'' of th