 EDITOR'S NOTE _ He was introduced to music at the <ORGANIZATION> Holiness </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Birmingham </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ala. </LOCATION>, and a <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> nun in <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> taught him to play the snare drum. He would go on to play with such jazz greats as <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Armstrong </PERSON> and <PERSON> Benny </PERSON> <PERSON> Goodman </PERSON> and eventually form his own band. A half-century later, <PERSON> Lionel </PERSON> <PERSON> Hampton </PERSON> is still on the road, playing his kind of music.
