<TEXT>
 Back-to-back increases in new home sales have pushed such sales to the highest levels since August, the government says. The 4 percent rise in new homes sales in March followed a 14.1 percent jump the previous month, the departments of Housing and Urban Development, and <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> said Friday. But some analysts are worried that rising mortgage rates could limit growth in the second half of the year.
