 <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banking </ORGANIZATION> boards in March, and began its tender offer shortly after. <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION>'s stock purchase is part of a complex restructuring proposed by <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> that includes several cost-cutting measures and asset sales. To that end, <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> said it will sell its 39 percent equity interest in <LOCATION> Banca </LOCATION> <LOCATION> della </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Svizzera </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Italiana </LOCATION> to the Swiss-based financial firm <ORGANIZATION> Unigestion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SA </ORGANIZATION> for $ 390 million in cash. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> estimates a pre-tax gain of $ 136 million, or $ 5 per share, from the transaction. The bank also said it would sell its 50-story building at One Wall Street. Both transactions are expected to fund the special $ 10 dividend payout. Irving Chairman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Rice </PERSON> said in a statement that the bank's board `` greatly appreciates the willingness of BCI to improve its offer. If the deal were consumated, <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> would have the right to buy an additional 10 percent of Irving stock on the open market.
