 <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cos. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> announced Monday that its executive committee had elected <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Rosenwald </PERSON>, Jr. vice chairman and <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Cayne </PERSON> president Bear <PERSON> Stearns </PERSON>, a publicly traded financial company, is the <ORGANIZATION> parent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a major investment and brokerage firm Both positions, which are new, will apply to both the parent company and the brokerage subsidiary. Both men will continue as members of the board of directors and executive committee of the parent and as senior managing directors of <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Rosenwald </PERSON> and <PERSON> Cayne </PERSON> have been members of the office of the president since October 1985 when <PERSON> Bear </PERSON> <PERSON> Stearns </PERSON> became a public company, but that office has been eliminated <PERSON> Rosenwald </PERSON>, 58, has headed the company's corporate <ORGANIZATION> finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> department </ORGANIZATION> since 1976 and is the senior investment banker in the department. He joined <PERSON> Bear </PERSON> <PERSON> Stearns </PERSON> in 1954, first as a research analyst and later in its international department. <PERSON> Rosenwald </PERSON> headed institutional sales for 20 years before moving to corporate finance. He became a general partner of Bear Stearns in 1962. <PERSON> Cayne </PERSON>, 54, is manager of the company's <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> branch system and is responsible for individual investor sales. He started at <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> in 1969 as a salesman for individual investors and became a general partner in 1973, building the retail business into a major division. The chairman and chief executive officer of <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Companies </ORGANIZATION> is <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Greenberg </PERSON>; the executive vice president and chief operating officer is <PERSON> Alvin </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Einbender </PERSON>.
