<HEAD>Executive Recruiter Accused of Insider Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> on Monday accused a <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> man of violating insider trading regulations by making stock profits based on information he learned in his job as head of a corporate recruiting firm. The <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> civil complaint accused <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ingoldsby </PERSON> of making $ 14,000 in profit in trading shares of stock in <ORGANIZATION> Artel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a fiber optics company with headquarters in <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> charged that <PERSON> Ingoldsby </PERSON>, the head of an executive search firm located in <LOCATION> Wellesley </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, was hired by <ORGANIZATION> Artel </ORGANIZATION> in September 1986 to find a new chief executive for the company. <PERSON> Ingoldsby </PERSON> allegedly purchased 23,500 shares of <ORGANIZATION> Artel </ORGANIZATION> stock after learning that <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bowman </PERSON>, an executive he had recruited to head <ORGANIZATION> Artel </ORGANIZATION>, was about to accept the top post at the company. The <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> complaint, which was filed in federal court in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, seeks an injunction barring Ingoldsby from violating insider-trading regulations in the future and seeks fines equal to the $ 14,000 he allegedly made in profit in trading <ORGANIZATION> Artel </ORGANIZATION> stock. <PERSON> Ingoldsby </PERSON>, the head of <ORGANIZATION> Michael </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> O. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ingoldsby </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZAT